<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67a5fc5-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7111"><num value="7111">§ 7111.</num><heading> Oral examinations for licenses</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An individual may take an oral examination for a license to serve on a fishing, fish processing, or fish tender vessel not required to be inspected under part B of this subtitle.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf67a5fc6-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/541">97 Stat. 541</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/98/364/tIV/s402/8/B">Pub. L. 98–364, title IV, § 402(8)(B)</ref>, <date date="1984-07-17">July 17, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/447">98 Stat. 447</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/307/s1/10">Pub. L. 99–307, § 1(10)</ref>, <date date="1986-05-19">May 19, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/445">100 Stat. 445</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
